      <scopecontent id="aspace_2bbecf29ae8a35dbdff5c7087df76f63">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>This model represents a cross-section of the Yale Center for British Art. It was created and donated to the Center by Lindsay Falck's architecture students at the University of Pennsylvania School of Design.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <bioghist id="aspace_a686fc11e91e6bd86b04be137c720f32">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Dyer Alfred "Lindsay" Falck is a Lecturer at the University of Pennsylvania School of Design, PennDesign.  This model was made and donated to the Center by three of his students, Harry Lam, Cass Turner, and Greg Whitney, in the second year Case Studies Course at the Department of Architecture.</p>  
      </bioghist>
